FBIS3-51670 "drlat015_o_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Colombia FARC Kidnapping Retaliation PA2301043194 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 18 Jan 94 p 7 PA2301043194 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Briefs" column] [Text] Guerrillas presumed to be members of the FARC [Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia] on 17 January on the outskirts of Villavicencio kidnapped two U.S. citizens who were with an evangelical mission, apparently in reprisal for the presence of U.S. troops in Colombia. According to the authorities, the subversives entered La Esperanza estate in the capital of Meta, subdued its residents, and after identifying each of them kidnapped Americans Timothy Bay and Stevel Welth. [names as published]
